<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-541-313  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 541 313.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Lotus shipping Lotus MarketPlace: Business product. (a databaseprospect list for selling to businesses) (Lotus Development Corp.)andO;(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lotus Development Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    LOTS.andO;Product:   Lotus MarketPlace: Business (Data base) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData basesSalesSoftware PublishersCD-ROM.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>LOTUS SHIPPING LOTUS MARKETPLACE: BUSINESS PRODUCT CAMBRIDGE, MASSACHUSETTS,U.S.A., 1990 OCT 3 (NB) -- Lotus Development has begun shipping LotusMarketPlace: Business, the first member of its new family of sales andmarketing tools.andP;  The program uses the Apple Macintosh and CD-ROM to delivera database prospect list of names, addresses, telephone numbers, andmarketing data on seven million US businesses.andM;According to Frank Ingari, vice president of Lotus's Emerging MarketsBusiness Group, &quot;MarketPlace is unique among desktop software applicationsbecause it delivers a hard return on investment to businesses by dramaticallyreducing the cost, complexity, and time involved in finding new customers.andO;It's the first new approach in years to meeting a universal businesschallenge; identifying the best prospects for your products and services.&quot;andM;Lotus MarketPlace is available through Lotus-authorized dealers at asuggested retail price of $695 for the software, sample data, a data orderform, documentation, and the purchase of the first 5,000 names of choice fromthe compact disc.andP;  MarketPlace data will be updated quarterly.andP;  Users willhave the option to convert to an annual subscription with four additionalquarterly updates ($150 annually) or to replenish the meter with more namesfor use with the current disc at $400 for $5,000 additional names.andM;System requirements for using Lotus MarketPlace include an Apple Macintoshwith a hard drive, 4 MB (megabytes) of RAM (random access memory), Hypercard,and an Apple CD SC drive or 100 percent compatible.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19901002/Press Contact: Pamela Cay, Lotus Development,617-693-1305)</TEXT></DOC>